# CVE-2026-33186 - google.golang.org/grpc: authorization bypass via HTTP/2 path validation
# Component: SOPS binary (built from source in Docker image)
# Justification: This CVE affects gRPC server-side authorization. SOPS uses
#   gRPC exclusively as a client to call GCP KMS. No gRPC server is exposed,
#   so the attack vector does not apply.
# Review date: 2026-04-21
# Action: Remove this entry when SOPS releases a version with grpc >= 1.79.3
CVE-2026-33186

# CVE-2026-39883 - go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk: vulnerability in OTel SDK
# Component: SOPS binary (built from source in Docker image)
# Justification: OTel SDK is a transitive dependency of GCP client libraries
#   in SOPS. SOPS runs as a short-lived CLI process with no OTel exporters
#   configured (no OTEL_* env vars set). The library is compiled in but
#   effectively dormant. No network exposure.
# Review date: 2026-04-21
# Action: Remove this entry when SOPS releases a version with otel/sdk >= 1.43.0
CVE-2026-39883

# CVE-2026-34986 - github.com/go-jose/go-jose/v4: DoS via crafted JWE object
# Component: SOPS binary (built from source in Docker image)
# Justification: SOPS does not process JWE objects from untrusted sources.
#   go-jose is a transitive dependency used for auth with cloud KMS providers.
#   The DoS attack vector requires attacker-controlled JWE input, which does
#   not exist in our usage.
# Review date: 2026-04-21
# Action: Remove this entry when SOPS releases a version with go-jose >= 4.1.4
CVE-2026-34986

# GHSA-xmrv-pmrh-hhx2 - github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/service/s3: vulnerability in AWS S3 SDK
# Component: SOPS binary (built from source in Docker image)
# Justification: SOPS supports S3 as an optional backend, but this project
#   uses SOPS exclusively for GCP KMS encryption of local YAML files.
#   The S3 SDK code path is never invoked.
# Review date: 2026-04-21
# Action: Remove this entry when SOPS releases a version with aws-sdk-go-v2/service/s3 >= 1.97.3
GHSA-xmrv-pmrh-hhx2